      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GOOD VIBES (5) is racing in top order this time in work, winning comfortably fresh before settling last and never really threatening last time out. Cheung remains in the saddle and she boasts a strong record over this course and distance. The claim comes in handy and she can return to winning ways. HE'S ARCHIE (6) will find this much easier than what he's been racing in recently. He never really got into the race last time out, but he's better suited here fresh and he's a course and distance winner in the past. Ticks plenty of boxes. THREE GRAND (7) was out of the money two runs back then again missed the frame last start over 1500m at Albany, beaten 2.5 lengths into eighth. This doesn't look as hard so she is set to turn things around. PRETTY DEVINE (1) raced on the pace last start before fading to finish fourth, beaten 6 lengths, over 1200m at York. Sharni Webster who has three wins when partnering stays on. Has claims on her best figures. ON THE FULL (3) is not to be discounted.",
